# Create Package Documentation

When asked to create documentation for a package, read and follow the skill at `.claude/skills/docs-create-package/SKILL.md`.

Key points:
- Use the package template at `docs/templates/package-template.md`.
- Read `docs/guidelines.md` for style rules.
- Research the package by reading its README, Makefile, package.json, BFF directory, and frontend source — only read files and directories that exist; skip missing ones.
- Write the doc at `packages/<name>/docs/overview.md`.
- Omit template sections that don't apply — no "Not applicable" filler.
- Automatically update `BOOKMARKS.md` with the new entry.
